reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This was easier to set up than I thought
reviews.reviewText: I am not a app person at all, so I liked that I could set this up without using an app. It took me longer than it should have though because I am so used to set up being harder than it actually was. Go figure. So far it has been working very well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Another great product from Netgear!
reviews.reviewText: The router was easy to setup and put into service. Saving $100 by buying a renewed product was the cherry on top. Performance and stability of router has been excellent, so far. I would recommend this option to anyone looking to upgrade their router at a reasonable price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very Cool But...
reviews.reviewText: Unfortunately does not support IPv6 ND Proxy that my Verizon 5G Home Internet requires or else IPv6 doesn't work. That's too big a drawback at this price to ignore, but it does seem like a cool unit overall if only it was compatible.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Way over priced for performance
reviews.reviewText: My xfinity xb8 isp provided gateway out performed this router and was more reliable. Obnoxiously large and minimal adjustments to the integrated antennas.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Solid little router
reviews.reviewText: Great little home router. The QoS settings are horrible and the DHCP resevation pool is bareley functional. But everything else is great. Supports 2.5g into the router then you have to use port aggregation with two LAN ports to get 2 gigs out. It is far from am enterprise level router but is works great for home use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars easy setup, item like new

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Slower speeds than my regular 6
reviews.reviewText: Had slower speeds than my netgear rax50. 2.4 kept disconnecting messing up all off my alexa devices, I had to re-pair all of my light bulbs and echos. Easy setup, great if you are upgrading from 5 but not from a 6. And yes all my devices are 6E compatible.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works Perfectly, Blazing Fast Internet
reviews.reviewText: I bought this router to replace my older nighthawk router that was starting to show its age.Since I already had a nighthawk and the companion app, setting up the new router was a breeze and took less than 10 minutes.All of my devices reconnected since my network name and password remained the same, but their output was improved noticably.Everything from streaming to video calls to normal Internet tasks went significantly faster and smoother, I've experienced no intermittent connection drops, and coverage distance has improved.Honestly, the best refurbished piece of equipment I've ever had, it might has well have been brand new!
